How to build DB12x (WASP) u-boot bootloader

1. download Atheros LSDK: lsdk.9.2.0.1020
2. extract it
3. go to boot/ directory
4. apply this patch (../lsdk.9.2.0.1020_wasp_ar8035_u-boot.diff)
5. go to ../build directory
6. make BOARD_TYPE=db12x  
   It will build toolchain stuff. 
   Do not worry if it will fail ath the end of compile. We need gcc stuff.
7. make uboot BOARD_TYPE=db12x ETH_CONFIG2=_ar8035
   It will build u-boot for WASP with:
   * external AR8035 PHY on MAC0
   * internal S27 PHY on MAC1
8. use ../boot/u-boot/u-boot.bin u-boot image to flash

